45周年

7
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,090
走吧 麦克斯
Come on, Max.

8
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:44,530
- 早上好 梅瑟夫人  - 喔 克里斯
- Morning, Mrs Mercer.  - Oh, Chris.

9
00:02:44,610 --> 00:02:46,110
你今天起得真早
You're early this morning.

10
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,490
我天刚亮的时候就被双胞胎吵醒了
I've got the twins waking me up at the crack of dawn.

11
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:50,250
我的天 我都忘了
Oh, my God, I completely forgot.

12
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,290
- 恭喜  - 谢谢
- Congratulations.  - Cheers.

13
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:54,750
- 你们俩日子怎么样？  - 事情多得可怕
- How are you both coping?  - It's a hell of a lot of work.

14
00:02:54,830 --> 00:02:56,130
那是肯定了
I don't doubt it a second.

15
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:58,670
但你没问题的 你是个能干的小伙子
But you'll be fine. You were always a capable young man.

16
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,050
你现在一定很兴奋吧
You must be getting excited.

17
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,750
- 周六 对吧？  - 别提了 还有一堆事情要做
- Saturday, isn't it?  - Don't remind me. So much work to do.

18
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,050
不过 没问题的
Yeah, it'll be fine.

19
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,880
- 祝你好运  - 谢谢
- Good luck.  - Thank you.

20
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:08,090
我真为你们俩高兴
And I'm really over the moon for both of you.

21
00:03:08,180 --> 00:03:10,850
- 谢谢 梅瑟夫人  - 凯特 叫我凯特就好
- Thank you, Mrs Mercer.  - Kate. Call me Kate.

22
00:03:10,930 --> 00:03:12,350
我们已经不是在学校里了
We're not at school any more.

23
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:14,230
好的
Will do.

24
00:03:48,050 --> 00:03:50,370
[The Platters 为美国黑人摇滚乐队]
[代表作《Only You》、《Smoke Gets in Your Eyes》]
你觉得 Platters 那首歌怎么样？
What do you think of that Platters song?

25
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,560
[The Platters 为美国黑人摇滚乐队]
[代表作《Only You》、《Smoke Gets in Your Eyes》]
- 什么怎么样？  - The Platters 的歌
- The what?  - The Platters song.

26
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:55,010
什么时候放？
What for?

27
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,850
跳第一支舞时放
First dance.

28
00:03:56,930 --> 00:03:59,860
还是你觉得我们婚礼上放的歌已经过时了？
Or think it's a bit naff to have the same song we had at our wedding?

29
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,480
不 这首歌很可爱
No. Lovely song.

30
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:04,360
- 我一直都很喜欢  - 我就知道
- I've always liked it.  - Yeah, I know.

31
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:17,080
♫ 人们曾经问我怎知 ♫
♪ Asked me how I knew ♪

32
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,710
♫ 我的爱情意真挚 ♫
♪ My true love was true ♪

33
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:38,850
- 这是什么？  - 一封信
- What is it?  - A letter.

34
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:41,980
嗯 我知道 谁寄的？
Yes, I know, but who from?

35
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:44,650
- 用德文写的  - 是啊
- It's in German.  - Yeah.

36
00:04:44,730 --> 00:04:46,820
写的什么？
What's it say?

37
00:04:47,730 --> 00:04:52,910
我记不清这些动词啊名词啊的意思了 但是…
Well, I can't remember the verbs as well as the nouns, but...

38
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:56,750
但我想上面写的是他们找到她了
but I think it says they've found her.

39
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,750
找到谁？
Found who?

40
00:04:58,830 --> 00:05:01,250
唔 准确说 是她的尸体
Well, her body, anyway.

41
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:03,420
天呐 是谁？杰夫
God, who? Geoff.

42
00:05:05,460 --> 00:05:07,550
他们找到了卡佳
T-They've found Katya.

43
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,050
噢
Oh.

44
00:05:11,130 --> 00:05:13,350
你知道我在说谁吗？
Y-You know who I'm talking about, don't you?

45
00:05:13,430 --> 00:05:14,600
当然
Of course.

46
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:17,770
因为 我记得我和你说过 一清二楚
'Cause, I-I remember telling you, clear as day.

47
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:20,400
我当然记得 我是说 这是很久以前的事了
Of course I remember. I mean, it was a long time ago.

48
00:05:20,470 --> 00:05:22,690
我就知道我和你说过我的卡佳
Yeah, I-I know I told you about my Katya.

49
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:31,780
她在那儿五十多年了 就像在冷冻库里一样
She's been there over 50 years, like something in the freezer.

50
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:35,250
现在他们找到她了
Now they've found her.

51
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:42,050
[图伦男子：自然环境下形成的木乃伊，死于公元前四世纪却在一九五〇年才被发现]
就像那个 呃 瑞典沼泽里的图伦男子
L-Like that, er, Tollund Man in the Swedish bog.

52
00:05:43,330 --> 00:05:44,630
其实是在丹麦被发现的
Well, Danish, actually.

53
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:46,580
- 嗯？  - 写进课本里好多年了
- Hm?  - It was on the curriculum for years.

54
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:48,790
我给三年级生教过这些
I taught it to the third-formers.

55
00:05:54,130 --> 00:05:56,230
我再去泡点茶
I'll make some more tea.

56
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:12,110
嗯 我还需要一本字典
Yeah, I'm going to need a dictionary.

57
00:06:14,530 --> 00:06:16,750
我不知道去哪找
I-I don't know where to look.

58
00:06:16,820 --> 00:06:19,080
你为什么不看看塑料箱子里呢？
Why don't you check in the plastic boxes?

59
00:06:34,380 --> 00:06:37,130
什么也没有 除了DIY书
Nothing. Nothing but "do-it-yourself" books.

60
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:47,980
就是这个
That's it.

61
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:49,940
是它
Yeah.

62
00:06:50,020 --> 00:06:52,120
啊 谢啦
Ah, thank you.

63
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:59,460
你看 现在是雪全都融化掉了
You see, what's happened is the snow has completely melted.

64
00:06:59,530 --> 00:07:01,880
只剩下了冰
All that's left is the ice.

65
00:07:01,950 --> 00:07:04,370
他们就是这么找到她的
A-And that's how they found her.

66
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:07,960
- 什么意思？  - 就是 她还在那儿
- What do you mean?  - Well, she's still there.

67
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,040
- 冻在冰里？  - 是的
- In the ice?  - Yeah.

68
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:14,180
顺流下来了一些 可以肯定 但那儿的水非常清澈
Way down, I'm sure, but the water is very pure up there.

69
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:17,130
一定是这样 所以他们才能看见她
It must be, so they can see her.

70
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:20,140
- 他们把她弄出来了吗？  - 还没
- Well, haven't they taken her out?  - Not yet.

71
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:21,390
为什么？
Why not?

72
00:07:21,470 --> 00:07:24,100
你想 她可是被冻在瑞士雪山的冰川里 凯特
Well, she's in a glacier in the Swiss mountains, Kate.

73
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:25,810
这可没那么容易
It can't be that easy.

74
00:07:25,890 --> 00:07:27,990
根本没有公路上去
There are no roads up there.

75
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,360
那他们怎么确定那个人是她？
So, how do they know it's her?

76
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:34,990
我是说 可能根本就不是她
I mean, it might not be her at all.

77
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:38,320
唔 我猜 根据事发地点 他们推测这个人是她
Well, they've made an assumption, I suppose, from where they found her.

78
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,750
可能他们从衣物分辨出是她
Maybe they can tell from what she's wearing.

79
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:42,450
从她的衣物？
From what she's wearing?

80
00:07:42,530 --> 00:07:48,380
噢 对 对 对 那些 飞行员… 冰岛的 应该是
Oh, yeah, yeah, th-those, er, airmen in... Iceland, I-I think it was

81
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:50,330
他们被保存得很完好
they were perfectly preserved.

82
00:07:50,420 --> 00:07:51,920
噢 我居然忘了
Oh, I don't remember that.

83
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,750
我看过这方面的资料
Yes. I saw a documentary on it.

84
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:59,180
他们因为被迅速冰冻 和死前看上去一模一样
They were the same as when they died because of how quickly they froze.

85
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,510
你觉得是这么回事吗？
And you think that's what's happened?

86
00:08:01,590 --> 00:08:04,310
嗯… 我不知道 但你可以想象
Well, I don't know, but you can imagine.

87
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:10,440
我不确定她也是那样 毕竟过了这么久
Not sure it works like that. Not after all this time.

88
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:13,070
不过那样会很奇怪吧？
How strange would that be, though?

89
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:16,200
她看着还是一九六二年那样
She'll look like she did in 1962.

90
00:08:16,860 --> 00:08:18,950
而我已经成了这副样子
And I look like this.

91
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:31,300
这是怎么啦？
What is it?

92
00:08:31,370 --> 00:08:33,470
呃 别生气 凯特
Er, don't be cross, Kate.

93
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:36,010
我要出去抽支烟
I'm going to have a smoke.

94
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:14,550
- 你还好吗？  - 嗯
- Are you all right?  - Fine.

95
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:20,090
把这个吃了 然后去吃药
Please eat this. And take your pills.

96
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:24,340
他们在信里问我是否想去瑞士
Th-They've asked if I want to go to Switzerland.

97
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:26,560
他们为什么问这个？
Why would they ask that?

98
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:28,730
嗯… 去确认尸体
Well, to see the body.

99
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:31,350
- 什么时候？  - 越快越好吧 我猜
- When?  - Soon, I suppose.

100
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:34,280
- 你不打算去吗？  - 不知道
- You aren't thinking of going?  - Don't know.

101
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:37,400
大老远去瑞士？
All the way to Switzerland?

102
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,820
也不是很远
It's not that far.

103
00:09:38,900 --> 00:09:40,570
有从斯坦斯特德机场起飞的航班
There are flights from Stansted.

104
00:09:40,650 --> 00:09:42,070
是 但也够远的了
Yeah, but it's far enough.

105
00:09:42,150 --> 00:09:44,030
- 你觉得我不应该去？  - 说实话？
- You don't think I should?  - Honestly?

106
00:09:44,110 --> 00:09:46,040
嗯 不应该去
Well, no.

107
00:09:46,110 --> 00:09:48,080
我不知道去的意义何在
I don't see the point.

108
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:51,330
- 再说我们在周六还有派对  - 我又不是说现在就走
- Plus we've got the party on Saturday.  - I wasn't thinking of going now.

109
00:09:51,410 --> 00:09:53,760
- 我不会现在就走的  - 是啊 但你一定会去
- I-I wouldn't go now.  - Yeah, but still.

110
00:09:53,830 --> 00:09:56,880
我不赞成你去爬那该死的大雪山
I don't like the idea of you climbing a big bloody mountain.

111
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:59,210
嗯 我觉得不会要爬山的
Well, I don't think it would come to that.

112
00:09:59,290 --> 00:10:01,550
你连跟我一起去布罗茨散步都不愿意
You don't like going for a walk with me on the Broads

113
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:03,030
那地方可是跟煎饼一样平
and that's as flat as a pancake.

114
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:03,760
我知道
I know.

115
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:07,310
我说啦 凯特 不会要爬山的
Like I said, Kate, it wouldn't come to that.

116
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:09,480
可还是…
But still...

117
00:10:11,470 --> 00:10:14,070
- 你不是要去镇上吗？  - 哦 我可以再找时间去
- Don't you have to go into town?  - Oh, I can rearrange.

118
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:16,270
别 你还是快去吧
No, y-you should go.

119
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:18,200
这事有点令人震惊 但仅此而已
It's been a bit of a shock, that's all.

120
00:10:18,270 --> 00:10:20,370
我没事儿
But I'm fine.

121
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,580
- 你确定吗？  - 是的 很好
- Are you sure?  - Yeah, positive.

122
00:11:02,480 --> 00:11:05,330
看起来大不一样了 空荡荡的
Oh. It looks different, all empty.

123
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,870
桌子一般放在这儿
Well, this is where the tables are usually placed.

124
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:11,670
主桌在这里 好让所有人都看得到你
The top one over there, so that everyone can see you.

125
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:14,160
谢了 但我们不需要主桌
We won't be having a top table, but thank you.

126
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:15,370
真的？
Really?

127
00:11:15,450 --> 00:11:17,960
在这样的场合一张主桌是极妙的
A top table is so lovely at an event like this.

128
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:20,340
你们俩就是全场焦点
The two of you as a focal point of the room.

129
00:11:20,420 --> 00:11:22,420
我们并不是要再来一次婚礼
We're not trying to recreate the wedding.

130
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,220
就是个派对
It's just a party.

131
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,510
好吧 当然 随你心意
Yes, well, it's your choice, of course.

132
00:11:27,630 --> 00:11:32,730
这地方棒极了 对周年纪念来说 绝对是个明智的选择
I will say, though, it's a wonderful place, location-wise, for an anniversary.

133
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,680
这是四十周年 是吧？
It's your 40th, isn't it?

134
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:35,980
四十五周年
45th.

135
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:38,150
这可是个不太寻常的庆祝节点
That's an unusual one to celebrate.

136
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:44,230
我丈夫当时生病取消了四十周年纪念 所以我们不得不改变计划
My husband was ill and our 40th was cancelled, so we had to rearrange.

137
00:11:45,110 --> 00:11:49,030
那么 我必须得尽量把这次办得非常特别 对吧？
Well, I must try and make this one super-special, then, mustn't I?

138
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:55,450
这儿绝对是举行周年纪念的绝佳地点
And this really is a great venue for such an event.

139
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:58,130
充满历史气息 是吧？
So full of history, you see?

140
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,370
像历久弥新的婚姻
Like a good marriage.

141
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:04,590
[特拉法尔加海战为英法两国的海上大战，最终英方取胜]
你知道特拉法尔加庆祝舞会就是在这里举行的吗？
Did you know that the Trafalgar Ball was held here?

142
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:05,970
知道 你的助手和我说了
Yes, your assistant told me.

143
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:07,970
那是一八〇五年
It was in 1805.

144
00:12:08,050 --> 00:12:10,390
你能想象当时的场景有多么壮观吗？
Can you imagine how incredible that must have been?

145
00:12:10,470 --> 00:12:15,470
[特拉法尔加战役：英国海军历史上最大的一次胜利]
[为英国奠定海上霸主的地位，但主帅纳尔逊被俘]
在场的每个人都盛装出席 庆祝这一伟大的胜利
Everyone here, dressed in their finest, celebrating such an achievement.

146
00:12:15,970 --> 00:12:18,070
纳尔逊不是被杀了吗？
Wasn't Nelson killed?

147
00:12:18,520 --> 00:12:20,390
但是我们赢得了战役啊
But the battle was won.

148
00:12:21,060 --> 00:12:24,410
非常值得庆贺 不是吗？
And that has to be worth celebrating, doesn't it?

149
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:32,370
我们的婚礼上有主桌 但是我们一点也不喜欢
We had a table at our wedding, a top table, but we didn't like it at all.

150
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:35,620
我丈夫认为这是腐朽的资产阶级糟粕
My husband thought it a horribly bourgeois tradition.

151
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:40,250
我们看看开胃菜菜单吧？
Shall we have a look at the canapé list?

152
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:42,130
呃 好的 当然
Er, yes, indeed.

153
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:44,300
我马上回来
I'll be right back.

154
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,590
不急
No rush.

155
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:04,840
这里是杰夫和凯特的家 请留言
You have reached Geoff and Kate. Please leave a message.

156
00:14:28,150 --> 00:14:30,700
你已经很久不听这首歌了
You haven't listened to this for a long time.

157
00:14:32,690 --> 00:14:35,120
- 你感觉怎么样？  - 我很好
- How are you feeling?  - I'm fine.

158
00:14:35,190 --> 00:14:36,700
你的手指怎么了？
What have you done to your finger?

159
00:14:36,780 --> 00:14:41,790
噢 嗯 我只是 呃… 想修理一下马桶 结果 呃 把自己大拇指给割了
Oh, yeah, I was, er... trying to mend the lavatory and, er, well, I cut me thumb.

160
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,750
你把它修好了吗？
Did you manage to fix it?

161
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:47,000
我想它需要一个新的浮球阀
It needs a new ballcock, I think.

162
00:14:48,710 --> 00:14:51,300
- 我之前打电话给你了  - 你留言了吗？
- Tried calling earlier on.  - Did you leave a message?

163
00:14:51,380 --> 00:14:53,510
没 我就是想问问你还好吗
No, I just wanted to check you were all right.

164
00:14:53,590 --> 00:14:55,590
好
Right.

165
00:15:00,430 --> 00:15:02,760
[索伦·奥贝·克尔凯郭尔为丹麦基督教思想家，存在主义先驱]
- 你在看什么？  - 克尔凯郭尔
- What are you reading?  - Kierkegaard.

166
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:05,360
[索伦·奥贝·克尔凯郭尔为丹麦基督教思想家，存在主义先驱]
天呐 你又在尝试看这本吗？
Gracious, are you having a go at that again?

167
00:15:07,020 --> 00:15:09,770
那本书你已经有三个不同版本了
You know, you have three editions of that book,

168
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:13,730
而且我觉得不管哪一版你连第二章都没读完过
and I don't think you've got past chapter two in any of them.

169
00:15:25,950 --> 00:15:28,170
真是奇怪的一天
Yeah, it's been an odd day.

170
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,000
是啊
It sure has.

171
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:34,710
我就是… 呆在家
I just, er... stayed at home,

172
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:37,140
你知道的 和浮球阀作斗争
you know, grappling with the ballcock.

173
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,140
但你是对的
But y-you're right.

174
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:40,560
我都不怎么去散步了
I hardly go walking any more.

175
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:44,230
今天天气好 所以我出去了
And it was a nice day, so off I went.

176
00:15:44,310 --> 00:15:46,770
- 那么你去哪儿了？  - 就去了村子里
- So, where did you go?  - Just to the village.

177
00:15:47,140 --> 00:15:48,770
去买烟？
To buy cigarettes?

178
00:15:51,190 --> 00:15:53,910
我还没嗅觉失灵呢 你知道吧？
I haven't lost my sense of smell, you know?

179
00:15:53,980 --> 00:15:56,910
我只是不希望我们又开始抽烟
I just don't want us to start smoking again.

180
00:15:56,990 --> 00:15:58,450
不 我不会 我不会的
No, I-I won't, I won't.

181
00:15:58,530 --> 00:15:59,750
我保证
I promise.

182
00:15:59,820 --> 00:16:01,820
好吧 继续说
OK. Go on.

183
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:07,000
我到了村子里 不知道怎么了
So, I was in the village, and I don't know what happened

184
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:10,330
遇见那个种族主义者从社区中心走出来…
but that racist from the community centre...

185
00:16:10,420 --> 00:16:12,040
嗯哼 桑德拉·威尔金斯
Mm. Sandra Wilkins.

186
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:14,220
对，是她
Yeah, her.

187
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:18,380
她向我走来 正对着我
She came up to me, right up to me face,

188
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:21,640
然后不断问我是否还好
and she kept asking me if I was all right.

189
00:16:22,930 --> 00:16:26,900
我说是的 但她不相信我
And when I said I was, she wouldn't believe me.

190
00:16:28,180 --> 00:16:30,780
况且… 我什么也没做
And... l wasn't doing anything.

191
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:36,740
什么也没做 就是坐在鸭子池边的长凳上
Nothing. Just sitting on the bench by the duck pond,

192
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:39,160
想点自己的事 呼吸点新鲜空气
minding me own business and getting some air.

193
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:41,620
就是这样
All done.

194
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,790
我就做了这些 我保证
All I was doing, I promise.

195
00:16:43,870 --> 00:16:45,410
我相信你
I believe you.

196
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:48,170
她是个可怕的女人
She's a dreadful woman.

197
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,340
- 别管她就是  - 嗯
- Just ignore her.  - Mm.

198
00:16:58,710 --> 00:17:00,340
这菜还行吧？
Is it all right?

199
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,770
很好吃 很好
Oh, it's great. Great.

200
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,940
嗯
Yeah. Mm.

201
00:17:05,930 --> 00:17:07,350
再来一杯？
A drop more?

202
00:17:07,430 --> 00:17:09,520
嗯 谢谢
Mm, thank you.

203
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:35,170
- 怎么了？  - 没事
- What?  - Nothing.

204
00:17:40,840 --> 00:17:44,640
- 我有些事想跟你说  - 说吧
- There's something I want to tell you.  - OK.

205
00:17:45,550 --> 00:17:48,270
知道吗 我很确信我之前跟你说过了
You know, I-I feel sure I've told you before,

206
00:17:48,350 --> 00:17:52,230
但那是很久之前了 所以 我有可能记错了
but it was a long time ago, so, I mean, I could be wrong.

207
00:17:57,730 --> 00:17:59,570
- 嗯 说吧  - 好
- OK, go on.  - Yeah.

208
00:17:59,650 --> 00:18:02,150
我算是她的直系亲属
Um, I-I was her next of kin.

209
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,660
什么意思？
What do you mean?

210
00:18:06,740 --> 00:18:08,710
唔 从官方上来说
Well, officially.

211
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:12,040
我算是她的直系亲属 我确定之前和你说过的 凯特
I-I was her next of kin. I'm sure I told you this before, Kate.

212
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:16,170
我想我会记得我丈夫是另外一个女人的直系亲属这种事的
I think I would remember my husband being another woman's next of kin.

213
00:18:19,210 --> 00:18:21,590
- 为什么？  - 什么为什么？
- Why?  - Why what?

214
00:18:21,670 --> 00:18:23,720
为什么你算是她的直系亲属？
Well, why were you her next of kin?

215
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:26,100
因为他们觉得我们已经结婚了
Because they thought we were married.

216
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:29,350
- 谁？  - 官方 人们
- Who did?   - The authorities. People.

217
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:30,730
他们为什么会这么认为？
What made them think that?

218
00:18:30,810 --> 00:18:32,900
我们跟他们是这么说的
We-We told them we were.

219
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,980
但你们没有 对吧？
You weren't, though?

220
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:38,560
噢 没没没 没有 当然没有
Oh, no, no, no. No, h-hell, no.

221
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:41,780
我们必须假装 这样别人才会让我们借住他们的房子
We just had to pretend, so people would let us stay in their houses.

222
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:46,060
那会儿和现在不一样 凯特 然后… 就是那场事故
Different in those days, Kate, and then after... the accident.

223
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:51,330
你没骗我？
You're not lying to me?

224
00:18:51,410 --> 00:18:54,960
没有 凯特 她手上戴了一个戒指
No. Kate, she wore a ring on her finger.

225
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:59,790
小巧的木制戒指 像窗帘环一样 橡木制的
It was a small wooden ring, like a curtain ring, made of oak.

226
00:19:01,670 --> 00:19:03,050
你还记得这些细节 真有意思
Funny you'd remember that.

227
00:19:03,130 --> 00:19:05,220
那不算是真的
Well, it wasn't real.

228
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:18,230
好吧 你可以… 你可以早点告诉我的 杰夫
OK, you could've... you could've just told me, Geoff.

229
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:22,450
我以为我已经说过了
I thought I had.

230
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:28,000
如果我还没说 那么 这挺难的 呃…
If I hadn't, well, it's hardly, er...

231
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,240
把这种事告诉
the sort of thing you tell

232
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:34,790
你漂亮的新女友 不是吗？
your beautiful new girlfriend, is it?

233
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:40,510
我可不这么觉得
I suppose not.

234
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:48,350
我想我要… 上楼去然后洗个澡了
I think I'm going to have a... go upstairs and have a bath.

235
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:51,220
明天还有很多事要做呢
I've got lots to do tomorrow.

236
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:53,900
- 你确定你还好吗？  - 嗯 嗯
- Are you sure you're all right?   - Yes. Yes.

237
00:19:53,970 --> 00:19:55,140
嗯 真的 挺好的
Yeah, really, I am.

238
00:19:55,220 --> 00:19:58,650
我不能为咱们相遇之前发生的事生气 不是吗？
I can hardly be cross with something that happened before we existed, can I?

239
00:19:58,730 --> 00:20:00,820
也不是这么说
Not really.

240
00:20:02,730 --> 00:20:04,730
但是…
Still...

241
00:20:49,240 --> 00:20:51,700
我想你现在都不愿意抱我了吧
I suppose a cuddle's out of the question.

242
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:08,300
我甚至觉得当时在那儿的根本不是我
It doesn't even feel like it was me that was there.

243
00:21:09,130 --> 00:21:11,130
你明白我的意思吗？
Do you know what I mean?

244
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:12,840
你在那待了多久？
How long had you been up there?

245
00:21:12,930 --> 00:21:15,640
六周还是七周吧 估计
Oh, six or seven weeks, I suppose.

246
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,810
或许更久
It seemed a lot longer.

247
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:21,270
我们出发时带了张地图
We had a map, er, to start with.

248
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:24,070
那玩意真他娘的不靠谱
It was so bloody unreliable.

249
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:26,950
不过我还是到了一个地方
I've still got it somewhere.

250
00:21:27,820 --> 00:21:31,290
我们往山上更高的地方爬去
Yeah, we were getting higher into the mountains

251
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:36,210
我觉得最好得找个人
and I decided it would be best if we found someone,

252
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:40,000
你知道的 帮我们到意大利边境
y-you know, to help us get to the Italian border.

253
00:21:40,490 --> 00:21:43,090
- 一个导游？  - 对 但不是真正的导游
- A guide?  - Yeah, wasn't really a guide.

254
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:47,300
[杰克·凯鲁亚克：美国著名小说家，代表作《在路上》]
这个黑皮小杂种觉得自己是杰克·凯鲁亚克
This swarthy little bastard who thought he was Jack Kerouac.

255
00:21:47,300 --> 00:21:50,630
[杰克·凯鲁亚克：美国著名小说家，代表作《在路上》]
- 你一直都特讨厌凯鲁亚克  - 是啊 没错
- You always did hate Kerouac.  - Yes, I did.

256
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,630
也许你就是嫉妒了
Maybe you were jealous.

257
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,940
- 什么 嫉妒杰克·凯鲁亚克？  - 嫉妒那个导游
- What, of Jack Kerouac?  - Of the guide.

258
00:21:58,010 --> 00:21:59,430
他在和她调情吗？
Was he flirting with her?

259
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:03,440
嗯 他们是有 呃… 在言语上
Well, they did have, er... the language.

260
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:07,490
我的德语 不那么好 带口音
My German, it wasn't that great, what with its accent.

261
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,400
他们常常笑话这个
They laughed a lot.

262
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:13,160
他永远只会开一些我不知道有什么好笑的玩笑
He was forever making these jokes I didn't get.

263
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:16,740
- 天呐 你可不喜欢这样  - 不 我不喜欢
- Oh, God, you wouldn't like that.  - No, I didn't.

264
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:23,760
他们一起在我前边走着 比必要的距离更往前
They were walking up ahead, more than they needed to perhaps,

265
00:22:23,830 --> 00:22:28,010
或许… 我就随他们去了吧 我不知道
or... maybe I just let them, I don't know.

266
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:33,140
我们到了一个沿着岩石的小道
We were on a track round this rock,

267
00:22:34,130 --> 00:22:38,430
冰川就在我们的右下方
and the glacier was on the right, below us.

268
00:22:39,430 --> 00:22:41,150
我们沿路而下
Way down.

269
00:22:41,220 --> 00:22:43,440
景色宜人
Beautiful thing, it was.

270
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:45,770
你会喜欢那儿的风景的 凯特
You'd love the landscape out there, Kate.

271
00:22:45,850 --> 00:22:47,950
- 你真的会喜欢的  - 嗯 我相信
- You really would.  - Yeah, I'm sure.

272
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:54,370
他们离开了我的视线 走到了拐角处
They were out of sight, round the corner,

273
00:22:56,110 --> 00:23:00,870
我最后听见的是她的笑声
and the last sound but one that I heard was her laughter.

274
00:23:01,660 --> 00:23:04,880
天呐 这笑声真是让我恼火
And, Christ, did it annoy me.

275
00:23:07,040 --> 00:23:09,130
但是不久 就传来了尖叫声
But then, there was a scream.

276
00:23:10,380 --> 00:23:12,470
但这叫声并不响
It wasn't a loud scream, neither.

277
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:18,770
我估计是空气从她受到冲击的肺里倾泻而出
Sort of outpouring of air from her lungs from the shock, I suppose.

278
00:23:19,930 --> 00:23:22,020
很低沉的喉音
It was low and guttural,

279
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:27,610
根本不像她的声音 柔软的 尖尖的
not like her voice, which was soft, higher-pitched.

280
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:32,410
天呐 太可怕了
God, that's just horrible.

281
00:23:32,690 --> 00:23:35,070
嗯 嗯
Mm. Mm.

282
00:23:35,150 --> 00:23:36,740
然后呢？
And then what?

283
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:38,700
就这样 无力回天
That was it, really.

284
00:23:38,780 --> 00:23:40,830
等我到那里 她已经不见了
When I got there, she'd gone.

285
00:23:42,490 --> 00:23:44,710
凯鲁亚克朝着那个洞望去
And Kerouac was looking down this hole.

286
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,960
一条裂缝
A fissure.

287
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:53,510
是的 裂缝 可以这么说 就像一块岩石从中间裂开
Yeah, a fissure, I suppose you'd call it, like a narrow, narrow crack in the rock.

288
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:56,880
你还记得在苏格兰那个吗？
D-Do you remember that one in Scotland?

289
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:01,350
- 嗯 我记得  - 对 就跟那个一样
- Yeah, I do.  - Yeah. Well, it was like that one.

290
00:24:01,430 --> 00:24:04,270
- 嗯  - 只是深得多
- Yeah.  - Only much deeper.

291
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,820
凯鲁亚克就站在那里
And Kerouac was just standing there.

292
00:24:09,730 --> 00:24:14,110
他的脸 扭曲发黄
His face, oddly enough, it looked almost yellow.

293
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,540
她是金发吗？
Was she blonde?

294
00:24:21,610 --> 00:24:23,660
- 什么？  - 她有一头金发吗？
- Sorry?  - Did she have blonde hair?

295
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,460
噢 不 不 她是黑发
Oh, no, no. She had dark hair.

296
00:24:26,540 --> 00:24:27,790
- 像我一样  - 嗯
- Like mine, then.  - Mm.

297
00:24:27,870 --> 00:24:29,960
我是说 不是现在
I mean, not now.

298
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:32,590
是啊 像你一样
Yeah, like yours.

299
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:35,800
她当时多大？
How old was she?

300
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:42,480
她比我大两岁 当时是六二年
She was two years older than me, and that was '62.

301
00:24:42,550 --> 00:24:44,550
嗯 那她当时大概二十七岁
Yeah, so she was about 27.

302
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:46,730
对
Yeah.

303
00:24:48,180 --> 00:24:50,530
我妈妈是那年去世的
My mum died that year.

304
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,480
- 是吗？  - 是的 嗯
- Did she?  - Yeah. Mm.

305
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:55,610
- 我不知道为什么这很可笑但确实如此  - 可笑？
- I don't know why that's funny but it is.  - Funny?

306
00:24:55,690 --> 00:24:59,820
唔 我们当时互相不认识 你和我
Well, we didn't know each other then, you and I,

307
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:04,080
但我们却同时经历着令人心碎的事 并且…
but we were both going through something really unpleasant, and...

308
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:08,410
我们相识了这么些年 还从没跟对方提起过
and yet we never talked about it in all the years that we've known each other.

309
00:25:08,490 --> 00:25:11,960
- 从没  - 没有 从来没有
- Never.  - No. Never have.

310
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:31,190
我累了
I'm tired.

311
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:34,560
我要关灯吗？
Shall I turn off the light?

312
00:25:35,480 --> 00:25:37,570
嗯
Yeah.

313
00:25:50,410 --> 00:25:52,510
我也很累了
I'm quite tired, too.

314
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:06,370
星期二

315
00:26:16,020 --> 00:26:17,740
过来
Come on.

316
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:20,740
麦克斯！
Max!

317
00:26:27,990 --> 00:26:29,120
麦克斯！
Max!

318
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:31,670
孩子！过来！
Yeah, boy! Come on!

319
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:33,840
过来！乖孩子
Come on! Good boy.

320
00:27:02,150 --> 00:27:03,450
你今天起得真早
You're up early this morning.

321
00:27:03,530 --> 00:27:06,450
是啊 我想我可能和你一起去镇上 如果你不介意的话
Yeah, I thought I might come into town with you, if you don't mind.

322
00:27:06,530 --> 00:27:07,700
不 当然不介意
No, of course I don't mind.

323
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:11,130
我想去买个新的浮球阀
Yeah, I-I want to go to Thorns, get a new ballcock.

324
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:13,290
好啊
Oh, good.

325
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:20,500
你觉得我的图书馆卡还能用吗 凯特？
Do you think my library card will still be valid, Kate?

326
00:27:21,290 --> 00:27:24,640
- 没什么不能用的啊  - 如果有时间的话我想去那转转
- I don't see why not.   - I might pop in there if there's time.

327
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:26,810
随便看看
