Oh, he'll be all right.

387
00:30:57,260 --> 00:30:59,510
不管怎样 他有了发泄的机会
Anyway, it gives him a chance to vent.

388
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:01,350
- 发泄什么？  - 关于你
- About what?  - About you.

389
00:31:01,430 --> 00:31:02,760
妈！
Mum!

390
00:31:02,850 --> 00:31:05,680
也不是说关于你 不过跟派对有关
Not about you as such, but about the party.

391
00:31:05,770 --> 00:31:07,980
你说他要发泄跟派对有关的事… 是什么意思？
What do you mean about... vent about the party?

392
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:10,770
我想起乔治在我们的四十周年纪念前有多糟糕
When I think how awful George was before our 40th,

393
00:31:10,860 --> 00:31:12,650
我差点就跟他离婚了
I was that close to divorcing him.

394
00:31:12,730 --> 00:31:14,070
别管她
Ignore her.

395
00:31:14,150 --> 00:31:17,030
那么 你打算穿什么礼服？你喜欢什么样的？
So, what's going to happen with your dress? What would you like?

396
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:25,290
所以 我们不该办派对吗？
So, should I not be having a party?

397
00:31:25,790 --> 00:31:27,080
当然要有
Of course you should.

398
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,960
我们两个都很有压力
It is a lot of pressure for both of us.

399
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:31,330
而且不管怎样我都讨厌派对 就算是在最好的日子
And I hate parties anyway, at the best of times.

400
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:33,630
我说 我都从来没有开派对庆祝过自己的生日
I mean, I never even celebrate my birthday.

401
00:31:33,710 --> 00:31:36,090
不 不 不 不 不 你得开
No, no, no, no, no, you have to.

402
00:31:36,170 --> 00:31:38,050
我说 怪就怪在这儿
I mean, that's the strange thing.

403
00:31:38,130 --> 00:31:41,640
乔治是很糟糕 但你记得他到了派对上的样子吗？
George was awful, but then do you remember him at the actual party?

404
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:43,220
他哭的有多厉害？
How much he cried?

405
00:31:43,300 --> 00:31:45,390
还不仅仅是在致辞的时候哭
And not only during the speeches.

406
00:31:46,640 --> 00:31:49,270
是啊 他是个很动情的人
Yeah, he was very sweet.

407
00:31:50,190 --> 00:31:51,940
这就是为什么派对这种事情很重要
That's why these things are important.

408
00:31:52,020 --> 00:31:53,610
什么 为了让丈夫们哭吗？
What, to make our husbands cry?

409
00:31:53,690 --> 00:31:56,980
不光是丈夫们 所有的男人
Not just husbands, all men.

410
00:31:57,690 --> 00:31:58,620
他们总是最先被触动的人
It's always them that break first.

411
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:02,320
莎莉的婚礼 查理的洗礼
Sally's wedding, Charley's christening.

412
00:32:02,410 --> 00:32:05,910
我们能一起操办起来 是因为我们早就知道这些事情的重要性
We hold it together 'cause we already know how important these things are.

413
00:32:08,580 --> 00:32:11,250
杰夫可不是爱哭鬼
Geoff is not much of a crier.

414
00:32:11,330 --> 00:32:13,420
我打赌他在婚礼上哭了
I bet he cried at your wedding.

415
00:32:14,290 --> 00:32:16,380
我不记得了
I don't remember.

416
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:23,550
如果这是某种进化的关键
If it's some twist of evolution

417
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:28,100
让男人们把一门心思花在讣告和分配遗产上
that needs men to be obsessed by their obituaries, their legacies,

418
00:32:28,180 --> 00:32:32,270
