Don't think so.

561
00:44:24,940 --> 00:44:26,150
我去跟他说
I'll speak to him.

562
00:44:26,230 --> 00:44:27,820
呃 也许这没什么大不了的
Er, maybe it doesn't matter.

563
00:44:27,900 --> 00:44:29,990
不 我去跟他说
No, I'll speak to him.

564
00:44:42,170 --> 00:44:43,330
女士们…
Ladies...

565
00:44:43,420 --> 00:44:45,960
倒满吗？
Full, full?

566
00:44:46,050 --> 00:44:48,170
还要加点牛奶吗？
Do you want more milk?

567
00:44:50,930 --> 00:44:52,840
好的
Yes.

568
00:44:53,430 --> 00:44:55,260
来点饼干？不要了吗？
Biscuit? No?

569
00:44:57,350 --> 00:44:58,600
不要？
No?

570
00:44:58,680 --> 00:45:01,140
那我把饼干放这儿 我自己要拿一块吃
Well, I'll leave them there. And I'll take one.

571
00:45:01,230 --> 00:45:02,770
- 谢谢你  - 在这之后
- Thank you.  - After that,

572
00:45:02,850 --> 00:45:05,980
商人们通过这条新开辟的航线进行生意往来
the merchants used these newly created waterways,

573
00:45:06,070 --> 00:45:10,110
航道被逐年加深拓宽
and over the years they were cut deeper and wider,

574
00:45:10,190 --> 00:45:12,780
这就是为什么布罗茨会成为今天的面貌
and this is why the Broads are as they are today

575
00:45:12,860 --> 00:45:14,610
供大家欣赏
for all of you to enjoy.

576
00:45:15,320 --> 00:45:20,200
试想一下如果罗马人在别处发现了泥炭
Now, just imagine if those Romans had found peat elsewhere

577
00:45:20,290 --> 00:45:23,790
或是决定在国土上的其它地方开挖泥炭
or chosen to dig in another part of the country.

578
00:45:23,870 --> 00:45:25,960
那这些航道也就不会存在了
Then these broads wouldn't be here at all.

579
00:47:04,480 --> 00:47:06,560
那是杰夫吗？
Is that Geoff?

580
00:47:06,850 --> 00:47:08,600
是的 是他
Yes, it is, yeah.

581
00:47:08,690 --> 00:47:10,770
他在做什么？
What's he doing?

582
00:47:11,070 --> 00:47:12,980
他又抽烟了吗？
Is he smoking again?

583
00:47:13,070 --> 00:47:15,190
看上去是
Looks like it.

584
00:47:18,450 --> 00:47:21,240
在派对那天之前你该让他把胡子刮了
You should get him to shave before the big day too.

585
00:47:41,680 --> 00:47:44,310
- 你好 杰夫里  - 你好 莉娜
- Hello, Geoffrey.  - Hello, Lena.

586
00:47:45,930 --> 00:47:48,020
希望你已经准备好你的致辞了
Hope you've got your speech prepared.

587
00:47:48,100 --> 00:47:50,900
我想在星期六听到你赞美凯特的话
I want to hear nice things about Kate on Saturday.

588
00:47:58,570 --> 00:48:01,570
我听说你不想去克劳利家吃午餐
So, I hear you don't want to go to the Crawley's lunch.

589
00:48:04,660 --> 00:48:07,080
你不去没关系 但我想知道原因
I don't mind if you don't, but I wondered why.

590
00:48:07,160 --> 00:48:09,250
我就是不想去
I just don't.

591
00:48:09,870 --> 00:48:12,330
你一直都很期待和大家再次碰面啊
You've been looking forward to seeing everyone again.

592
00:48:12,420 --> 00:48:14,380
这件事你都念叨好几个星期了
You've been talking about it for weeks.

593
00:48:15,710 --> 00:48:18,670
- 为什么不想去了？  - 我有我的原因
- Why don't you want to go?  - I've got me reasons.

594
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:19,970
什么原因？
Which are?

595
00:48:20,050 --> 00:48:22,550
我去不去跟你有什么关系？
Why does it matter to you if I go or not?

596
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:24,390
和我没关系 但都已经安排好了
It doesn't, but it's been arranged.

597
00:48:24,470 --> 00:48:25,560
所以呢？
So?

598
00:48:25,640 --> 00:48:30,560
所以你不能言而无信 仅仅因为你不想去做
So you can't just back out of things simply because you don't feel like it.

599
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:32,730
即使你有你的原因
Even when you have reasons.

600
00:48:39,030 --> 00:48:41,320
乔治他也会很不开心的
And George will be very upset.

601
00:48:41,410 --> 00:48:44,740
他… 他好几周前就开始计划这次聚会了
He's... well, he's been organising it for weeks.

602
00:48:44,830 --> 00:48:46,910
- 他是你的朋友  - 喔 好吧
- And he's your friend.  - Oh, fine.

603
00:48:47,660 --> 00:48:50,660
- 那你会去吗？  - 我就是那么说的 不是吗？
- Then you'll go?  - Well, that's what I said, didn't I?

604
00:48:56,670 --> 00:49:02,090
有些天 我们完全忘掉了去意大利事 停滞不前
Some days, we forgot all about getting to Italy. Just stayed put.

605
00:49:02,180 --> 00:49:04,220
我们变得漫不经心
We were being heedless.

606
00:49:04,300 --> 00:49:06,890
这是我能找到的最合适的词
I think that's the word I'm looking for.

607
00:49:06,970 --> 00:49:08,180
漫不经心？
Heedless?

608
00:49:08,270 --> 00:49:10,350
漫不经心
Heedless.

609
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:12,940
在她的家乡 柏林墙正被筑起
Back in her Berlin, the Wall was going up

610
00:49:13,020 --> 00:49:16,480
[猪湾事件：美国阴谋以武力支持古巴流亡者颠覆古巴革命政权]
而在美国刚发生了猪湾事件
and in America we'd just had the Bay of Pigs.

611
00:49:17,730 --> 00:49:22,030
但那会儿 我们根本不管那些
But up there, we weren't thinking about all that.

612
00:49:22,700 --> 00:49:25,490
也不去想我们的未来
Weren't thinking about our future.

613
00:49:26,490 --> 00:49:28,700
但与此同时 我们也根本没有漫不经心
But, at the same time, we weren't heedless at all.

614
00:49:28,790 --> 00:49:31,660
你怎么可能漫不经心？当你清楚自己的目标时
How can you be when, when you know what your purpose is?

615
00:49:31,750 --> 00:49:34,920
当每一天似乎都有着某种意义时
When every day seems to have some point to it.

616
00:49:35,000 --> 00:49:37,340
寻找安顿之处 寻找食物
Finding somewhere to stay, finding food.

617
00:49:38,420 --> 00:49:40,510
那些日子里我们哪儿都没去
And the days we didn't go anywhere,

618
00:49:40,630 --> 00:49:42,090
但它们就是好像充满了目标
they seemed just as purposeful

619
00:49:42,170 --> 00:49:47,470
就像在该死的清晨四点雄赳赳地启程那样
as when we set out in complete seriousness at four in the fucking morning.

620
00:49:48,510 --> 00:49:54,560
我想 嗯… 我想衰老最可怕的地方莫过于
I-I think, um... I think that's the worst part of getting decrepit,

621
00:49:54,650 --> 00:49:58,270
失去那种… 目的性
losing that... purposefulness.

622
00:49:59,980 --> 00:50:04,530
今天我想起了我们之前看到过的那些花儿
I-I was remembering today how we used to see these flowers.

623
00:50:05,280 --> 00:50:07,740
紫罗兰的一种吧 我想是的
Some sort of violet, I think they were.

624
00:50:08,660 --> 00:50:13,200
它们会找到一小块雪融掉的草地
They'd find a patch of grass where the snow had melted

625
00:50:13,290 --> 00:50:15,370
然后就茁壮成长
and they'd just spring up.

626
00:50:15,750 --> 00:50:19,840
我知道它们只是花朵 但它们看上去那么坚定
I know they were only flowers, but they seemed so determined.

627
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:22,000
甚至可以说 勇敢
Brave, even.

628
00:50:22,760 --> 00:50:25,590
我觉得卡佳和我就是那样
And that's how I see Katya and me.

629
00:50:26,720 --> 00:50:31,510
游走四方 摒弃现代文明
Wandering around, turning our backs on civilization.

630
00:50:32,180 --> 00:50:34,020
勇敢？
Brave?

631
00:50:34,100 --> 00:50:36,190
可以这么说
In a way.

632
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:38,230
你不觉得吗？
Don't you think?

633
00:50:38,310 --> 00:50:39,810
并不
Not really.

634
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:41,860
为什么不？
Why not?

635
00:50:41,940 --> 00:50:44,400
我说 你们究竟在干什么？
I mean, what were you actually doing?

636
00:50:44,490 --> 00:50:47,150
你们只是在爬某座该死的山罢了
You're just climbing up some bloody mountain.

637
00:50:48,530 --> 00:50:51,620
当然 我不是说我们这么做是出于勇敢
Well, I'm not saying what we did was out of bravery.

638
00:50:54,790 --> 00:50:58,170
我觉得 你只是在追一个想要被追的女孩而已
I think you were just chasing a girl who wanted to be chased.

639
00:51:05,840 --> 00:51:07,680
你不了解她
You didn't know her.

640
00:51:08,510 --> 00:51:10,510
是
No.

641
00:51:11,180 --> 00:51:13,260
我不了解
I didn't.

642
00:51:15,390 --> 00:51:17,480
我累了
I'm tired

643
00:51:18,770 --> 00:51:21,400
睡之前我想问你个问题
I want to ask you something before we go to sleep.

644
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:23,570
什么问题？
What's that?

645
00:51:27,070 --> 00:51:32,120
如果她没死 如果你们到了意大利
If she hadn't died, if you had got to Italy,

646
00:51:32,200 --> 00:51:34,330
那你会真的娶她吗？
would you have married her for real?

647
00:51:36,250 --> 00:51:38,910
但我们没能到意大利 不是吗？
But we didn't get to Italy, did we?

648
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:40,460
而且她确实死了
And she did die.

649
00:51:40,540 --> 00:51:42,460
嗯 但是如果呢
Yeah, but if you had.

650
00:51:42,540 --> 00:51:46,800
我以为你不喜欢这种假设的问题
I thought you didn't like theoretical questions.

651
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:48,920
只管回答我
Just answer me.

652
00:51:49,760 --> 00:51:51,840
是的
Yes.

653
00:51:57,140 --> 00:51:59,140
是 你就会娶她？
Yes, you would have married her?

654
00:51:59,230 --> 00:52:01,060
是的
Yes.

655
00:52:02,310 --> 00:52:04,400
我就会娶她 她就会嫁给我
We would have married each other.

656
00:52:17,870 --> 00:52:20,290
我觉得我再也没法谈论她的事了
I don't think I can talk about her any more.

657
00:52:22,290 --> 00:52:26,340
我知道我说过可以 但现在我办不到
I know I said I could, but I can't.

658
00:52:39,050 --> 00:52:44,000
星期四

659
00:53:56,970 --> 00:53:58,640
那边还有你认识的人吗？
Anyone you know still there?

660
00:53:58,720 --> 00:54:00,810
什么？没了 都是新人
What? No, they're all new.

661
00:54:10,900 --> 00:54:12,610
好吧 那 过会儿见
OK, then, I'll see you later.

662
00:54:12,690 --> 00:54:14,450
嗯
Yeah.

663
00:54:14,530 --> 00:54:16,610
等等
Hang on.

664
00:54:17,990 --> 00:54:19,490
试着让自己开心点
Just try and enjoy yourself today.

665
00:54:19,580 --> 00:54:21,660
嗯 我尽量
Yeah. I'll try.

666
